      "message": "It seems to me that on line 242, 'sequence.split(...)' will always return at least one entry, so there will be at least one attempt to go through the loop. If it then makes it out of the loop without returning (or an exception), 'current' and 'last' will both be set to non-null values. In any case, this test doesn't hurt, and probably makes Sonar happy.",
